# PR Workflow

## Branch naming
`feat/<skill-name>-<short-description>` or `fix/<skill-name>-<short-description>`

Examples:
- `feat/import-commit-hygiene`
- `fix/tdd-classicist-tier-matrix`

## PR title
Conventional commit format: `feat(tdd-classicist): add regression-fix checklist`

## PR body template

```markdown
## What
Brief description of what changed.

## Skills affected
- `skill-name` (version X.Y.Z → A.B.C)

## Checklist
- [ ] `skill-registry.json` updated
- [ ] `metadata.json` version matches registry
- [ ] SKILL.md under 500 lines
- [ ] `bash scripts/skill-sync.sh --list` shows correct state
- [ ] No secrets or credentials in skill content
```

## When importing skills from other repos
- Use `scripts/skill-import.sh` to ensure consistent structure
- Verify the imported SKILL.md frontmatter is valid
- Add meaningful tags in the registry entry
- Single commit for import + registry update
